						<summary>

						<p>On a stone lying outside the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1423, Durmati, Śrāvaṇa, śu. 5, [Friday], corresponding to 1501 A.D., July 20, Tuesday.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Records the consecration of the image of Hanumān by [Nā]vayya, the <hi rend="italic">karaṇam</hi> of Chintalapūṁḍi in Kōṭabhūmi belonging to Śrīraṅgarāja, for the merit of his brother Rāghavayya.</p>						

						</summary>
